video_title: Agents Unleashed Podcast Ep. 1 - Builder's Night Wrapup
description:
This is episode one of the Agents Unleashed podcast â€” a show all about the latest developments in the fast-paced world of agentic AI.

This episode is a recap of some highlights from the last Agents Unleashed event, held March 1st during ETHDenver. 
Chapters

00:00 Introduction 
01:51 Haseeb on true AI agents vs chatbots
03:12 Three-level taxonomy of AI agents
05:08 Rate Rover: Autonomous DeFi agent spotlight
06:49 The Nevermined payment layer for AI agents
08:12 The Combinder agent for HVAC optimization
10:11 8baller presents the Validation Station: Decentralized RPC provider
11:51 Scientific AI agents from Bio Protocol
14:00 Future outlook and next episode preview


Agents Unleashed is an ongoing event series focused on AI agents. Events have been held in 6 cities and counting, with 77+ speakers and over 2500 total attendees. To find out more about the next event, head to https://olas.network/agents-unleashed. 

Several clips are excerpted. If you'd like to watch the full talks, you can find that on the official Agents Unleashed playlist: https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLoP4p0r-X94q7eRSr-tr79asIfBIqMRtN

Sponsored by Olas, the best way to own and monetize your AI agents. Get the details at https://www.olas.network 

Theme music: "Forward" by Grand Project on Pixabay: https://pixabay.com/users/grand_project-19033897/
